    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    ArchiveChapter
    This class is a data model for an AO3 chapter.
    ArchiveComment
    This class is a data model for an AO3 comment.
    ArchiveController
    This class configures where different services can be reached through the server REST API.
    ArchiveDriverService
    This class is the Spring Boot service responsible for creating Selenium drivers.
    ArchiveElementNotFoundException
    This exception is used to indicate when a NoSuchElementException is thrown by the ArchiveIngestor.
    ArchiveIngestor
    This class is the primary parsing utility for ingesting AO3 stories and chapters.
    ArchiveIngestorCanceledException
    This exception is used to indicate when a parse session is canceled.
    ArchiveIngestorTest
    This test class is used to run unit tests and integration tests for the ArchiveIngestor class/service.
    ArchiveLogService
    This class is the Spring Boot service responsible for logging messages.
    ArchiveMessageService
    This class is the Spring Boot service responsible for storing standard messages for the server to use.
    ArchivePageNotFoundException
    This exception is used to indicate when the archive ingestor cannot find the requested story page.
    ArchiveParagraphsNotFoundException
    This exception is used to indicate when the archive ingestor cannot find the body of a story/chapter.
    ArchiveParse
    This class defines the JPA entity for an archive server parse.
    ArchiveParseRepository
    This interface defines extra methods for interacting with the table for ArchiveParse entities.
    ArchiveParseType
    This enum defines the parse types the archive ingestor application supports.
    ArchiveServer
    Top-level class that runs the Spring Boot backend using the @SpringBootApplication annotation.
    ArchiveServerAsyncConfig
    This class is the asynchronous configuration for the Spring Boot backend server.
    ArchiveServerAsyncExceptionHandler
    This class defines a custom AsyncUncaughtExceptionHandler for Archive Server application.
    ArchiveServerFutureData
    This class defines the POJO model for completable future data for the Archive Server.
    ArchiveServerRequestData
    This class defines the POJO model for POST request data for the Archive Server.
    ArchiveServerResponseData
    This class defines the POJO model for response data for the Archive Server.
    ArchiveServerSpecData
    This class defines the POJO model for archive server specification data.
    ArchiveServerTest
    This test class is used to run unit tests and integration tests for the ArchiveServer Spring Boot application.
    ArchiveServerTestData
    This class defines the POJO model for archive server test data.
    ArchiveServerWebsocketConfig
    This class defines the websocket configuration for the Archive Server application.
    ArchiveService
    This class is the Spring Boot service responsible for top-level actions used by the archive server controller.
    ArchiveSession
    This class defines the JPA entity for an archive server session.
    ArchiveSessionRepository
    This interface defines extra methods for interacting with the table for ArchiveSession entities.
    ArchiveSessionService
    This class is the Spring Boot service responsible for managing interacting with active and completed sessions.
    ArchiveStory
    This class is a data model for an AO3 story.
    ArchiveStoryInfo
    This class is a data model for AO3 story metadata.
    ArchiveVersionIncompatibleException
    This exception is used to indicate when the archive ingestor detects an incompatible AO3 website version.
    ArchiveWebsocketService
    This class is the Spring Boot service responsible for running live websocket feeds for active sessions.
    TestChannelInterceptor
    This test class implements a custom ChannelInterceptor for testing the archive server websocket.
